"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-30-Nadal-fell-to-Djkokovic-in-their-60th-meeting-at-Paris-Olympics-1vEZFPPvdtK-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Sports Scene  Copied  Rafael Nadal fell to Novak Djokovic in the second round in what was their 60th career meeting but only the second on the Olympic stage. The match also marked possibly the last chapter in one of the sport's most storied rivalries between the 38-year-old Spaniard who owns 22 Grand Slam titles, and the 37-year-old Serb with 24.  Djokovic dominated early, winning 10 of the first 11 games and eventually took a 6-1, 6-4 victory. The win avenged his loss to Nadal in the semifinals of the 2008 Beijing Olympics.  Meanwhile, Spain's Carlos Alcaraz did what his legendary compatriot could not do and advanced to the last 16 by defeating Dutchman Tallon Griekspoor 6-1, 7-6.  On the women's side, top seeded Pole Iga Swiatek eased past the host nation's Diane Parry 6-1, 6-1, setting up a third-round clash with China's Wang Xiyu, who got past Russian Diana Shnaider 6-3, 6-1.  Another Chinese, Zheng Qinwen also had a successful day, defeating Dutchwoman Rus Arantx-a 6-2, 6-4, and will next face American Emma Navarro.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"